{
  "_comment": "Copy to .mcp.json and set your server. The Mac's Claude launches the MCP server ON the Hetzner box over SSH and pipes its stdio back — no exposed port, no extra auth, uses your SSH key. For LOCAL use on the box itself, replace command/args with: \"command\": \"/usr/local/bin/meme-expert\", \"args\": [\"mcp\"].",
  "mcpServers": {
    "meme-expert": {
      "command": "ssh",
      "args": [
        "meme@YOUR_SERVER_IP",
        "MEME_SNAPSHOT_PATH=/home/meme/meme-expert/data/snapshot.duckdb /usr/local/bin/meme-expert mcp"
      ]
    }
  }
}
